   <mods:abstract>William just left for school, and should be better about writing all of
            them but does not have the habit of it yet formed. Believes he will finish his studies
            at Yale with æreputationÆ. His plans are still unchanged for the future, and John Jay
            approves of them, but it is best not to write of them yet. It has rained so much the
            bridge between the farm and the town in Bedford has washed out. The Munro family just
            came to visit. Frederick Jay has stomach trouble and probably does not get enough
            exercise. Regrets the illness of Mr. Constable and the troubles in Mr. VanderheydenÆs
            family. As life is a period of probation, they must expect trials along the way. NancyÆs
            eyes are worse some days and better others.</mods:abstract>
